theorem Topology.closure_eq_closure_inter_union_closure_diff {X : Type*}
    [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X} :
    closure (A : Set X) = closure (A ∩ B) ∪ closure (A \ B) := by
  -- Step 1: decompose `A` as the union of `A ∩ B` and `A \ B`.
  have h_decomp : (A : Set X) = (A ∩ B) ∪ (A \ B) := by
    ext x
    constructor
    · intro hxA
      by_cases hxB : x ∈ B
      · exact Or.inl ⟨hxA, hxB⟩
      · exact Or.inr ⟨hxA, hxB⟩
    · intro hx
      cases hx with
      | inl hAB => exact hAB.1
      | inr hA_diff => exact hA_diff.1
  -- Step 2: rewrite the left-hand side and use `closure_union`.
  simpa [h_decomp] using
    (closure_union : closure ((A ∩ B : Set X) ∪ (A \ B)) =
      closure (A ∩ B) ∪ closure (A \ B))

theorem Topology.closure_inter_subset_left {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A B : Set X} :
    closure ((A ∩ B) : Set X) ⊆ closure (A : Set X) := by
  -- `A ∩ B` is contained in `A`, so applying `closure` (a monotone operator)
  -- yields the desired inclusion.
  exact closure_mono (Set.inter_subset_left : (A ∩ B : Set X) ⊆ A)
